# LucidGate example list: requestregexsubstitutionlist
# Format: One regexp streaming substitution per line: pattern => replacement. Use bounded regexes; max window is configured in TOML for inline rules.
# Lines beginning with # are comments and are ignored by the loader.
# Request-body mutation is risky: broad rules can break CSRF tokens, signed JSON/protobuf payloads and browser forms.
# To activate a rule, copy one surgical example, remove the leading # and adapt it to your environment.
# You can include another file with: .Include<relative-or-absolute-path>
#
# Surgical commented examples:
#
# OpenAI API keys.
# \bsk-(?:proj-)?[A-Za-z0-9_-]{20,}\b => [REDACTED_OPENAI_KEY]
#
# Google OAuth access tokens.
# \bya29\.[A-Za-z0-9_-]{20,}\b => [REDACTED_GCP_TOKEN]
#
# HashiCorp Vault tokens.
# \b(?:s|hvs)\.[A-Za-z0-9_-]{24,}\b => [REDACTED_VAULT_TOKEN]
#
# Labeled secrets in text, JSON, query strings and form bodies.
# The regexp does not consume the final delimiter, so JSON quotes, form separators and newlines survive length-preserved replacement.
# (^|[^a-zA-Z0-9]|%[0-9a-fA-F]{2})((?i:password|passwd|secret|api_key|secret_key|auth_token|private_key))((?:\s*|%20|\+)*(?:"|%22|'|%27)?(?::|=|%3[Aa]|%3[Dd])(?:\s*|%20|\+|"|%22)*)((?:[^&%"'\n\r]+|%(?:[1-9A-Fa-f][0-9A-Fa-f]|0[0-9B-CE-Fa-f]|2[013-57-9A-Fa-f]))+) => ${1}${2}${3}[REDACTED_SECRET]
#
# Internal corporate domains. Replace company.com/corp before enabling.
# (?i)\b[a-z0-9-]+(?:\.[a-z0-9-]+)*\.internal\.(?:company\.com|corp)\b => [INTERNAL_DOMAIN_REDACTED]
#
# URL rewrite example. Keep host-specific to avoid mutating arbitrary URLs.
# https?://old\.example\.test/([^\s"']+) => https://new.example.test/$1
